==English==

===Pronounciation===
{{rfap}}

===Etymology===
Taken from Yiddish ''kvetsh'': an adjective describing a complainer or fault finder.
Previous to that it comes from German ''[[quetsche]]'' for [[crusher]] or [[presser]].
From Yiddish it has found its way into U.S. slang as a term of abuse.

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg-es}} 

# Person who endlessly whines or complains.
# Person who finds fault with anything.

===Adjective===
'''kvetch'''  (''no'' {{compar}} ''or'' {{superl}})

# Describing a kvetch or kvetcher.

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-sibilant|kvet|ch|}}

# To whine or complain, often needlessly.

